news.title: NCLT approves scheme of arrangement between Dalmia Bharat's subsidiaries
news.para: The Scheme, which comes into effect from the appointed date of March 31, 2023, was sanctioned under Sections 230 to 232 of the Companies Act, 2013.

news.title: Chandigarh administration may hike property tax for FY26
news.para: A special committee, headed by the UT finance secretary, has determined that the city's current property tax, calculated at 3% of annual ratable value, is lower compared to neighbouring and other major cities.

news.title: Chandigarh administration issues fresh guidelines for demolition of illegal structures
news.para: The DC office must also designate a nodal officer to communicate the information of demolition to relevant authorities, mentioning the specific violations while issuing demolition orders.

news.title: UBS considers sale of some real estate assets in Switzerland: Sources
news.para: The business area under review includes mainly Swiss real estate assets and, according to one of the people who declined to be named because the matter is private, could be worth less than $1 billion.

news.title: UK's Savills expects employees' return-to-office to boost real estate
news.para: Savills has been grappling with weakness in China and delays to some transactions in North America, while bond market turbulence earlier this year dented investor sentiment.

news.title: Topsoe leases 75,000 sq ft office space from Table Space in Noida
news.para: The company is a global leader in developing technologies that drive the energy transition, supporting industries in achieving sustainability and carbon reduction goals.

news.title: Raipur's Dantewada district digitizes over seven lakh land records
news.para: Blockchain technology, known for its security and resistance to tampering, is increasingly being adopted across various sectors, including land record management.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir government identifies 625 acres of land for industrial estates
news.para: The government has granted 36 limestone mining leases, 24 gypsum mining leases, and 202 e-auctioned minor mineral blocks, he said.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh's 2025-26 budget prioritizes urban development with major allocations
news.para: Urban transformation programmes receive notable attention, with Rs 1,071 crore allocated to AMRUT 2.0 and Rs 1,000 crore to Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0 BLC.

news.title: Bihar government extends deadline for land survey till December 2026
news.para: "The department has decided to extend the July 2026 deadline for the completion of the ongoing work of the survey and settlement of lands across the state by five months

news.title: UK's housing market reports slowest month in February 2025: Survey
news.para: The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors said buyer demand was the weakest since November 2023 and a further softening was expected in the months ahead.

news.title: Nilgiris administration begins crackdown on unauthorized buildings
news.para: Additional collector H R Kaushik said other identified unauthorized buildings in the district would also be sealed in the coming days. "Legal procedures for the same are under way," he said.

news.title: Nashik civic body to conduct survey to identify untaxed properties
news.para: Khatri's instructions came during a recent meeting with these private agencies. These agencies have already received work orders from the NMC and will start their work from April 1.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh governor distributes certificates, house keys to beneficiaries in Mirzapur
news.para: ​​The Governor praised the work of the Green Army in addressing social issues and stressed the importance of education for both boys and girls.

news.title: Amaravati capital progress drives real estate boom near Vijayawada West Bypass
news.para: The sector had faced stagnation during the previous government's tenure, as speculations about relocating the capital to Visakhapatnam discouraged investors.

news.title: Property registration locations in Indore merged for new guideline rates
news.para: The process has been undertaken through polygon mapping reducing the total number of registration locations from 5,124 to 4,613 in the city.

news.title: No flat 10% rise in RR rates across state: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: "There are news reports that the RR rate will be increased by 10-15%, but this is false. RR rates were last increased in 2022-23. A survey was carried out across the state, and I strictly warned there cannot be any arbitrary hike," he said.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB's sector 53 housing scheme’s future under cloud again
news.para: In the recently concluded demand survey for the scheme, nearly 7,500 applicants expressed their interest. In a previous survey (2018-19), the scheme received only 178 applications.

news.title: Mumbai: FIR against Wadhwa Group for cheating Policon Realtors of Rs 57 crore
news.para: ​The FIR alleged that Wadhwa Group directors, including Navin Makhija, failed to honour financial commitments made in the agreement despite receiving additional floor space index (FSI) and funds as part of a settlement deal.
